French Open
Nadal demolishes Federer in final
Ivanovic beats Safina in final
Roland Garros, Paris, 25 May-8 June
French Open official website
Men's final
Nadal
Federer
Photos
Women's final
Reaction
Photos
Third seed Jelena Jankovic is stretched by Romanian Monica Niculescu in a scrappy first set
But Jankovic - sporting some wacky nail varnish - eventually prevails 7-6 (7-3) 6-2 against the Roland Garros debutant
Marcos Baghdatis - the 17th seed - is unable to get past Simone Bolelli of Italy, losing in straight sets
Guillermo Coria's first visit to Roland Garros since 2006 ends in a battling four-set defeat to 12th seed Tommy Robredo
A rusty Venus Williams finds herself in a three-set battle with unheralded Israeli Tzipora Obziler but comes through in the end
World number one Roger Federer opens his campaign for a first French Open title with a straight-sets win over Sam Querrey
World number two Rafael Nadal is due to begin his title defence - but is held up by heavy rain in Paris
